folder: Goulden Avenue & Bedford Park Boulevard, Bronx, NY
original_title: Bronx: Goulden Avenue - Bedford Park Boulevard
text:
Goulden Ave. (running from right to left in center of view) between Bedford Park Boulevard and West 195th Street, showing the thoroughfare under construction. This area was formerly part of the Jerome Park Reservoir. The view is in a westerly direction.

April 27, 1936.

Works Progress Administration.
Federal Art Project photo.

Goulden Ave. (left, not seen), east side, between Bedford Park Boulevard and West 195th Street, showing one of the units of Hunter College being erected by the W.P.A. on what was formerly part of Jerome Park Reservoir.

April 27, 1936.

Works Progress Administration.
Federal Art Project photo.
title: Colleges and Universities - Hunter College - Golden Avenue E. between Bedford Park Boulevard and W. 195th Street - Bronx.

text:
Goulden Ave. (right, not seen), east side, between Bedford Park Boulevard and West 195th Street, showing one of the units of Hunter College and, in the background, the east wing of Walton High School and the 258th Field Artillery Armory. The Hunter College buildings were constructed by the W.P.A. on ground that was formerly part of the Jerome Park Reservoir. The view is southward.

April 27, 1936.

Works Progress Administration.
Federal Art Project photo.
title: Colleges and Universities - Hunter College - Golden Avenue E. between Bedford Park Boulevard and W. 195th Street - Bronx.
